    <text id="B0172T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brackett writes that he will be able to provide tuition and board for a girl
                    named Martha Strange, at his school in Harpers Ferry, West Virginia, apparently
                    at the request of Thomas Jackson.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Thomas">Tho</abbr> P. Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-12-06">Dec. 6, 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Harpers Ferry, <abbr expan="West Virginia">W. Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of <abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 2<hi rend="super">nd</hi> is before
                    me. We can furnish the girl of whom you speak for tuition, and a good room where
                    she can board herself <add hand="h1" place="inline">free of rent</add> This is
                    all we can do at present. <orig reg="Maybe">May be</orig> we can get some help
                    for her additional from the Peabody fund. We shall try with fair prospect of
                    sucess.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours in haste,</salute>
                    <signed>N. C. Brackett</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">We will furnish free tuition and room
                        <unclear>rent</unclear> &amp; several more. N.C.B.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
